    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "Praise belongs to Allah" }] },
    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "الحَمْدُ  لِلَّهِ" }] },
    {
      "words": [
        {
          "w": " Note that the word اللَّهُ becomes لِلَّهِ lillah-i(belongs to Allah) by just dropping the alif. No lam need to be added to the word. لِمَنْ means \"whose\" or \"belongs to whom\" e.g."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "mode": "text",
      "words": [{ "w": "Whose is this?(Whom does this belongs to?)" }]
    },
    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "لِمَنْ هَذَا " }] },
    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "Whose is the book?" }] },
    { "mode": "text", "words": [{ "w": "?لِمَنِ  الكِتَابُ" }] },
    {
      "words": [{ "w": "Note that مَنْ becomes مَنِ when followed by اَلْ " }]
    },
    { "words": [{ "w": "4. أَيْضًا means \"also\", e.g." }] },
